Public Protector Advocate Busisiwe Mkhwebane will hold a media briefing on Friday. Mkhwebane will release investigation reports into a number of probes she undertook. JOHANNESBURG - Public Protector Advocate Busisiwe Mkhwebane will hold a media briefing on Friday. Mkhwebane will release investigation reports into a number of probes she undertook. The Public Protector has been making headlines for being at loggerheads with Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan. This comes after her findings on Gordhan. WATCH: EFF unfazed as Ramaphosa, SACP defend Gordhan Mkhwebane wants President Cyril Ramaphosa to take remedial action against Gordhan after she found that he broke the rules when serving as SARS commissioner. However, Ramaphosa launched a court bid and maintains he cannot take action until a court finding. Mkhwebane says she is prepared to see the president in court.